com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers

Class ManagerRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<Manager>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers.ManagerRequestExecutor

  • public class ManagerRequestExecutor
extends RequestExecutor<Manager>
    Request executor provided by ManagersApi. Use this class if you want to get single manager through fluent API in chained fashion, for instance: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Manager manager = kontaktCloud.managers().fetch(ID).execute();
